<br>
Here are some tips to help NEWBIES, when you visit the BAZAAR.<br>
<br>
Upon entering the BAZAAR, you will notice that there is some LAG... did I mention that there was some LAG? &lt;hehehe&gt;<br>
HELPHELP:: Open your &quot;options&quot; and find your &quot;clip plane&quot;, move this to zero and you shouldn't have as much LAG.<br>
<br>
If you are here to BUY, do the following; Type  &quot;/bazaar&quot; (without the quotemarks). This will open a new window for you to use, &quot;the bazaar interface&quot;. You can search all the items available for sale, without even going into the BAZAAR. If an item isn't available that you are looking for, then you don't have to spend anymore of your time looking there. You can also research for items for different slots for your character or your alts. Great interface with some really good features. All kinds of search filters are available.<br>
<br>
Once you find some items that you are interested in, you can sort the list by NAME, PRICE and TRADER. Your can sort it backwards and forwards by clicking on the previously mentioned tabs above the list window. <br>
<br>
NOW, here is the fantastic part: Your can right click on an item in the list and get a view of what it is. WOW!!<br>
<br>
OK, so now you have found the exact item you want, at the price you want to pay and low and behold, you actually have the cash. SO, how in the heck do you find the TRADER that has the item for sale. (THIS IS THE COOLEST.) Just right click on the TRADER's name and you are pointed in his direction. If you run into a wall, then he must be on the other side, so just run around the wall and click again. This is much easier than trying to find someone by their LOCATION numbers. (This must be similar to the &quot;FIND CORPSE RODS&quot;.)<br>
<br>
If you are here to set up a TRADER: FIRST, you must buy at least one &quot;TRADER SATCHEL&quot; (you can have up to 8 stachels to list up to 80 single-stack items or you can have up to 1600 items in 80 stacks of 20), then type &quot;/trader&quot; (without the quotemarks) and you are on your way.<br>
<br>
1. Too set the price on an item you want to sell, just left click on the item with your mouse (it gets surrounded by a yellow square).<br>
2. Leftclick on the &quot;price&quot; boxes to set your prices in PP, GP, SP and CP amounts, click accept and you are on your way. (TIP: have a simple price, don't mix more then two types of monies in your price).<br>
3. After you have gone through and priced all your wares, you are ready to begin. First, find a location to set up. You have to setup under the &quot;awnings&quot;. (TIP: pick an uncrowed place away from the BANKs) Remember, part of the fun of buying is the SHOPPING.<br>
4. Hit the &quot;begin Trader&quot; button and you are off. You don't need any &quot;change&quot;, buyers must have the correct monies.<br>
Instructions are pretty straight forward, so good luck in selling your wares.<br>
5. You can change prices, add and subtract items from your inventory as you progress through the day/night, just remember to hit the add and &quot;list items&quot; buttons when you do.<br>
